 abstract = {© 2025 Copyright is held by the owner/author(s). Publication rights licensed to ACM.Recently, printed circuit board (PCB) placement has emerged as a significant challenge since the scale of PCB designs has rapidly enlarged. Furthermore, the presence of various types of constraints with differing tolerance priorities hampers the automation of PCB layout design, necessitating substantial manual effort. To address this problem, we introduce a novel agent-based framework that automatically generates PCB layouts meeting industrial constraints through user interactions. This framework includes two main agents: a reinforcement learning (RL)-based agent for layout inference and fine-tuning, and a large language model (LLM)-based agent for interactive optimization. Experimental results on 17 industrial tasks show that our framework outperforms other state-of-the-art methods.},
