@conference{Huang2025,
 abbrev_source_title = {Proc Des Autom Conf},
 abstract = {© 2025 IEEE.FinFlex standard cells have been proposed in sub-3 nm process nodes by TSMC to offer great design flexibility and a good trade-off between performance, power, and area efficiency. In the FinFlex technology, each cell type has a number of versions, varying in cell heights and threshold voltages, enabling flexible cell substitution for placement optimization. This paper presents the first work in the literature on standard cell legalization for the FinFlex technology, addressing cell version substitution, power efficiency, and minimum implant area (MIA) constraints. Our proposed algorithm comprises three stages: intra-row violationaware pre-processing considering timing and power levels, directed acyclic graph-based initial legalization with cell version substitution, and dynamic programming-based inter-row violation removal. Experimental results show the superior performance of our approach over a baseline using state-of-the-art techniques.},
